9 NEW SECTION. Section 9. Definitions. As used in [sections 1 through 9], the following definitions
10 apply:
11 (1) "Affiliate persons" means a person who owns more than 10% of a digital asset or network
12 token from the current available supply.
13 (2) "Blockchain" means data that is:
14 (a) shared across a peer-to-peer network to create a ledger of verified transactions or information
15 among network participants linked together using cryptography to maintain the integrity of the ledger and to
16 execute other functions; and
17 (b) distributed among network participants in an automated fashion to concurrently update network
18 participants on the state of the ledger and any other functions.
19 (3) "Blockchain protocol" means any executable software deployed to a blockchain, typically
20 referred to as smart contracts, including an additional standardized set of rules that uses a previously existing
21 blockchain as a base, which facilitates the transfer of data and electronic records and allows that data to be
22 broadcast to nodes. The executable software is governed by a set of predefined rules that execute
23 autonomously without human intervention. The rules may be altered by a predetermined mechanism.
24 (4) (a) "Central bank digital currency" means a digital currency, a digital medium of exchange, or a
25 digital monetary unit of account issued by the United States federal reserve system or a federal agency that is
26 made directly available to institutions or consumers by the entities, or which is processed or validated directly
27 by the entities.
28 (b) The term does not include a digital asset backed by legal tender or government treasuries and
